{
  "stem": "1753.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 114.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the gestapo, the civilian-- the secret police came and arrested us, picked us up right from the job, and took us to the central square of Karlsruhe, where the city hall and everything was located-- all the governmental buildings.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was a-- you know, the capital of the province of Baden.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there was a mob by the thousands.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we had to walk through that group of quote, unquote, 'mad people.' And they beat us, and made us bloody, and it was awful.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And a bunch of other Jews-- and finally, they took us to a horse barn, somewhere where the police had their horses, and-- and again mistreated us, and so on-- insulted us.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we had to face the walls.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And every few minutes, the-- over the loudspeaker, they had the loudspeaker saying, well, you don't have to cry.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It will be just a few more minutes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We'll shoot you to death.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And of course-- and I was screaming.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You know, I-- I couldn't take it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "It was awful for me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And-- and I got poked.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Don't scream, and then so on, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But in any case, late that night-- and it must have been about 10:00 or 11:00-- they picked out all the minors, including me, and sent them home, sent them back.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "My boss and, from that group, maybe 400 or 500 adult males were sent to Dachau.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "That was the first association I heard of Dachau.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We heard of Dachau.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "It was a penal camp for-- for-- for Jews and also for non-Jews that were against the Nazi regime.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And he was there.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
